  "text": "The SASL mechanism configuration validation in Apache Kafka at broker startup occurs through multiple coordinated components:\n\n1. **Configuration Definition and Validation (BrokerSecurityConfigs.java)**: Defines the SASL_ENABLED_MECHANISMS_CONFIG which specifies the list of SASL mechanisms enabled in the Kafka server. The SaslConfigs.java defines mechanism names including GSSAPI, and mechanism-specific configuration options like SASL_JAAS_CONFIG for SCRAM, GSSAPI, and OAUTHBEARER.\n\n2. **Broker Startup Validation (KafkaConfig.scala)**: The validateValues() method in KafkaConfig.scala performs critical validation at lines 627-629. It validates that the sasl.mechanism.inter.broker.protocol (inter-broker SASL mechanism) must be included in sasl.enabled.mechanisms when SASL is used for inter-broker communication. The saslEnabledMechanisms() function retrieves the enabled mechanisms for a listener.\n\n3. **JAAS Configuration Loading and Validation (JaasContext.java)**: The loadServerContext() method loads JAAS configuration at broker startup. It performs multiple validations:\n   - Ensures JAAS config property contains exactly one login module (throws IllegalArgumentException if zero or multiple modules)\n   - Validates that the login module is allowed via the DISALLOWED_LOGIN_MODULES system property\n   - For static JAAS configuration, verifies that the context name exists in the JAAS configuration file\n   - Throws ConfigException if JAAS configuration is malformed or missing required entries\n\n4. **JAAS Configuration Parsing (JaasConfig.java)**: Parses dynamic JAAS configuration from sasl.jaas.config property. Validates that:\n   - Login module class is specified\n   - Control flag (REQUIRED, REQUISITE, SUFFICIENT, OPTIONAL) is valid\n   - All option key-value pairs are properly formatted with semicolon termination\n\n5. **Channel Builder Setup (ChannelBuilders.java)**: The serverChannelBuilder() and create() methods load the enabled mechanisms list from BrokerSecurityConfigs.SASL_ENABLED_MECHANISMS_CONFIG and create JaasContext for each mechanism by calling JaasContext.loadServerContext().\n\n6. **Mechanism-Specific Handler Creation (SaslChannelBuilder.java)**: The configure() method iterates through each enabled mechanism and calls createServerCallbackHandlers(). This method creates mechanism-specific handlers:\n   - SCRAM mechanism: Creates ScramServerCallbackHandler\n   - GSSAPI mechanism: Validates Kerberos principal mapping rules, adds native GSS credentials\n   - OAUTHBEARER mechanism: Creates OAuthBearerUnsecuredValidatorCallbackHandler\n   - PLAIN mechanism: Creates PlainServerCallbackHandler\n   Each mechanism is validated and its corresponding callback handler is configured.\n\n7. **Login Manager Acquisition (LoginManager.java)**: The acquireLoginManager() method is called for each enabled mechanism during SaslChannelBuilder configuration (line 170 in SaslChannelBuilder.java). It validates the login module configuration and attempts to perform actual login via login.login(). If login fails, the LoginManager throws an exception that prevents broker startup.\n\nThe validation chain ensures: (1) sasl.enabled.mechanisms configuration is present and valid, (2) Each mechanism has corresponding JAAS configuration via sasl.jaas.config or system JAAS configuration, (3) Login modules are allowed and can be instantiated, (4) Mechanism-specific callback handlers are created and configured successfully."
}

